            "answer_text": "Open degrees are equal to regular degrees. The degrees offered by the Open and Distance Learning (ODL) schools which are registered under the Distance Education Council (DEC) in adherence to UGC Notification on Specification of Degrees are considered equivalent to those offered by the traditional Universities or Institutes in the country. The degrees offered by accredited open universities are valid and acceptable by the companies. However, it must be noted that the course must be completed from renowned universities like Venkateshwara Open University, etc because then only you get faster employability and advanced skill through training and real-life projects under the mentorship of highly-experienced teachers. ",
